1. CSS - cascading style sheet - it is used for styling website and making responsive website

2. css syntax :
    selector or group of selector{ property1 : value1; property2 : value2; property3 : value3}       

3. html code also called markup

4. three ways to add css to markup
    inline css   
    internal css  
    external css 

5. priority : external css ~ internal css(orderwise) < inline css : overwrite way 

6. chrome developer tools - inspect

7. web saved fonts - fonts which are preinstalled in most of the os 

8. web fonts - fonts which are imported from the internet to use ; visit google fonts and url to the html file

9. pixel - 1/96 of a inch

10. rgb has values from 0 to 256    

11. actual width of a element = padding+margin ; to eliminate this use box-sizing property

12. universal selector - using *

13. box or elements can be centered using auto in margin

14. display property - block or inline or inline-block;inline takes whole line ; block -can be use adjust width while inline cant be;
   

